Not physically.

But emotionally.

Nothing had resolved.

Everything had shifted.

Illuga stood alone in the corridor where it had all begun.

He hadn’t slept.

He hadn’t tried.

“You’re avoiding them.”

He didn’t need to turn to know who it was.

“…Observing,” Illuga corrected.

Siegurd stepped up beside him.

Not too close.

Never too close unless invited.

