SCENE 1 — AFTERMATH OF REVEAL (ZHAROSLAV / ILLUGA)
The monastery settles into a false quiet after the revelation. Snow thickens against the windows, turning the outside world into a shifting white void. Inside, heat clings low to the stone, never rising high enough to reach the vaulted ceiling.

Illuga returns to his chamber later than he intended.

The corridor is empty. Torches gutter in iron brackets, light stuttering with each push of wind through the cracks.

His door is closed this time.

He opens it.

Zharoslav is already inside.

Not waiting idly—standing near the hearth, one hand resting on the mantle as if the room belongs to him.

Illuga shuts the door behind him. The latch clicks. The sound feels final.

For a moment, neither speaks.

The fire pops. A small collapse of ember.

Illuga removes his gloves slowly, setting them aside with deliberate care.

“You’ve made a habit of this,” he says without looking up. “Entering rooms that aren’t yours.”

Zharoslav’s gaze tracks every movement.

“I go where I’m required.”

Illuga exhales through his nose—something between irritation and restraint.

“You’re not required here.”

A beat.

Zharoslav steps closer. Not abruptly—inevitably.

“That stopped being true tonight.”

Illuga finally looks at him.

There’s something different in Zharoslav now—not visible at a glance, but present in the way he holds himself. Tighter. More contained. As if something inside him has been sealed too quickly.

Illuga doesn’t like it.

“Say what you came to say.”

Zharoslav’s attention sharpens.

“You’re destabilizing the field.”

Illuga’s brow furrows. “That’s your concern?”

“It becomes my concern when it alters outcomes.”

“Flins being pregnant is not about you.”

“No,” Zharoslav says evenly. “It’s about what it proves.”

The air tightens.

Illuga straightens slightly. “And what does it prove?”

Zharoslav closes the remaining distance. Now they are within reach.

“That permanence can be created,” he says. “Even in circumstances that shouldn’t allow it.”

Illuga understands the direction of the conversation before the words fully land.

His jaw tightens.

“No.”

Zharoslav doesn’t pause.

“You felt it,” he continues. “The shift. The moment the room changed.”

“I said no.”

“And yet you’re still here.”

That lands harder than it should.

Illuga steps forward instead of back—closing what little distance remains.

“Don’t mistake proximity for agreement.”

Zharoslav’s hand lifts—not touching yet—hovering near Illuga’s jaw as if measuring the space.

“Don’t mistake resistance for refusal.”

Illuga catches his wrist before contact.

Firm.

Controlled.

“Careful.”

Zharoslav’s gaze drops briefly to where they’re connected.

Then back up.

“Then stop me.”

The challenge hangs between them.

Illuga’s grip tightens.

He could.

He knows it.

Zharoslav knows it.

And that’s exactly why he doesn’t move.

The silence stretches.

Breath slows.

Heat gathers—not from the fire.

Illuga releases him.

Not pushing away.

Just—letting go.

Zharoslav closes the final inch.

Contact.

Brief. Intentional. Electric in its restraint.

Illuga’s hand comes back up—but not to stop him this time.

It catches in his coat.

Anchors.

Their foreheads nearly touch.

“This ends badly,” Illuga says quietly.

Zharoslav’s answer is just as quiet.

“Only if you keep pretending you’re not choosing it.”

The shift happens there.

Not in force.

In recognition.

Illuga inhales.

Then—pulls him in the rest of the way.

The contact is not gentle.

Not taken.

Answered.

And once it starts—neither of them stops it.

SCENE 2 — SIEGURD (DEVOTION ESCALATION)
Night deepens. The monastery quiets to distant wind and the low murmur of banked fires.

Illuga sits at the edge of his bed, boots still on, posture rigid from a day that has not resolved.

A knock—soft, measured.

Siegurd does not enter until called.

“…Come in.”

He steps inside and closes the door behind him. He takes in the room quickly—not searching, assessing.

